Package edu.blackburn.cs.cs212.restaurantbase

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Orderable
    Defines required methods for an item to be orderable, that is, it can be added to a receipt.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Currency
    Represents a particular currency (for example, US dollars, Euros, Great British pounds)
    Measurement
    An abstract superclass for different types of measurement
    MenuItem
    Abstract superclass for all menu items at our restaurant; they have names and base prices
    Money
    Holds an amount of Money for a given Currency; uses a default of US Dollars if no currency is passed in.
    Receipt
    Generates a printable Receipt as a string from a given set of objects that implement Orderable
